uima.cas.Sofa.sofaString: A 57-year-old man with a structurally normal heart and normal baseline ECG underwent pulmonary vein isolation for atrial fibrillation. An electrophysiology study was then undertaken with an octapolar catheter positioned at the His bundle and an ablation catheter at the mid-right atrium.
